			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Heavy crude oil (or extra heavy crude oil) is highly viscous oil that cannot easily flow from production wells under normal reservoir conditions. It is referred to as 'heavy' because its density or specific gravity is higher than that of light crude oil. Heavy crude oil has been defined as any liquid petroleum with an API gravity less than 20°. Heavy oil is a type of crude oil that is different from conventional crude oil insofar as they are much more difficult to recover from the subsurface reservoir.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">重质原油（或特重质原油）是在正常储层条件下不易从生产井中流出的高粘度石油。之所以称为 &quot;重质&quot;，是因为其密度或比重高于轻质原油。重质原油被定义为 API 重力小于 20° 的任何液态石油。重油是一种不同于常规原油的原油，因为它们更难从地下储层中开采出来。</common:generalComment>
